events.1567: 25 July: Santiago de León de Caracas established by Spaniard Diego de Losada.
events.1577: Town becomes capital of Venezuela Province, Spanish Empire.
events.1595: Town captured by English troops led by George Somers and Amyas Preston.
events.1638: Roman Catholic Diocese of Caracas founded.
events.1749: 20 April: Economic demonstration led by Juan Francisco de León.
events.1777: City becomes capital of Captaincy General of Venezuela. Santa Rosalia parish established. City divided into eight administrative wards (barrios).
events.1779: Church of the Holy Trinity (Caracas) built.
events.1808: Gazeta de Caracas newspaper begins publication.
events.1811: City becomes capital of First Republic of Venezuela. Divina Pastora parish established.
events.1813: August: City taken by forces of Bolivar. City becomes capital of Second Republic of Venezuela.
events.1820: City becomes capital of Venezuela Department of Gran Colombia.
events.1835: Academia de Dibujo y Pintura (art academy) founded (approximate date).
events.1861: Colegio de Ingenieros de Venezuela established.
events.1874: National Pantheon of Venezuela established. Bolívar statue erected in Bolívar Square.
events.1881: Teatro Municipal de Caracas opens. City becomes part of the Distrito Federal de Venezuela. Population: 55,638.
events.1883: La Guaira-Caracas railway begins operating. Basilica of Santa Capilla (church) built. Academia Venezolana Correspondiente de la Real Española established.
events.1887: Academia de Musica y Declamacion (music school) and Academia de Bellas Artes (art school) active.
events.1889: Academia Nacional de la Historia de Venezuela inaugurated.
events.1928: Generation of 1928 anti-Gómez protest. Cine El Dorado (cinema) opens in San Agustín Parish.
events.1931: Caracas Athenaeum founded. Teatro Principal (Caracas) opens.
events.1937: Municipal Commission of Town Planning established.
events.1945: Simón Bolívar International Airport, Altamira Square, and Jardin Botanico de Caracas inaugurated. Caracas Journal newspaper begins publication.
events.1950: British School established. Population: 495,064 city; 693,896 urban agglomeration.
events.1952: Aerial Tramway begins operating. Estadio Universitario opens.
events.1953: Radio Caracas Televisión begins broadcasting. Cine Radio City (cinema) opens.
events.1959: La Rinconada Hippodrome opens in Coche Parish.
events.1963: December: Christmas display of illuminated Cruz del Ávila begins.
events.1973: Previsora Tower and Bet-El Synagogue built.
events.1974: Poliedro de Caracas (arena) opens. Museo de Arte Contemporáneo de Caracas opens.
events.1975: 28 October: 1975 Copa América football tournament held. Orquesta Sinfónica Simón Bolívar (youth orchestra) headquartered in city.
events.1979: El Diario de Caracas newspaper begins publication.
events.1983: Caracas Metro begins operating. Teresa Carreño Theatre and Brígido Iriarte Stadium open. Plaza Caracas and Parque Central Complex built. August: 1983 Pan American Games held.
events.1984: Mercantil Tower and Provincial Tower built.
events.1989: February: Protests. National Library of Venezuela building opens.
events.1990: Tower of David construction begins. Population: 1,824,892 city; 2,784,042 urban agglomeration.
events.1993: Mosque of Sheikh Ibrahim Al-Ibrahim built.
events.1999: Capital District (Venezuela) established. Movilnet Tower, and Centro Sambil (shopping mall) built.
events.2006: January: World Social Forum held. Libertador Simón Bolívar Terminal opens.
events.2007: May: RCTV closure demonstration. Squatters occupy Centro Financiero Confinanzas.
events.2008: Antonio Ledezma becomes mayor. Real Esppor football club formed.
events.2017: July: Strike in protest against president Maduro.
events.2019: January: Venezuelan Presidential crisis begins, leading to the 2019 Venezuelan protests.
